        "Question": "TRUE or FALSE. A suit for injunction is an action in rem. ",
        "Answer": "FALSE .A suit for injunction is an action in personam. In the early case of Auyong Hian v. Court of Tax Appeals (59 SCRA 110 [1974], it was held that a restraining order, like an injunction, operates upon a person. It is granted in the exercise of equity jurisdiction and has no in rem effect to invalidate an act done in contempt of an order of the court except where by statutory authorization, the decree is so framed as to act in rem on property. (Air Materiel Wing Savings and Loan Association, Inc. v. Manay, 535 SCRA356 [2007])."
