        "Answer": "NO. The complaint should not be dismissed because the mere non-joinder of an indispensable party is not a ground for the dismissal of the action (Sec. 11, Rule 3; Republic v. Hon. Mangotara, G.R. No. 170375, July 7, 2010)."
