        "Question": "Discuss the three (3) Stages of Court Diversion in connection with Alternative Dispute Resolution. ",
        "Answer": "The three stages of diversion are Court-Annexed Mediation (CAM), Judicial Dispute Resolution (JDR), and Appeals Court Mediation (ACM). During CAM, the judge refers the parties to the Philippine Mediation Center (PMC) for the mediation of their dispute by trained and accredited mediators. If CAM fails, the JDR is undertaken by the JDR judge, acting as a mediator-conciliator-early neutral evaluator. The third case is during appeal, where covered cases are referred to ACM."
