        "Answer": "The plaintiff should file a Motion for Judgment on the Pleadings because the failure of the defendant to answer a request for admission results to an implied admission of all the matters which an admission is requested. Hence, a motion for judgment on the pleadings is the appropriate remedy where the defendant is deemed to have admitted matters contained in the request for admission by the plaintiff (Rule 34 in connection with Sec. 2, Rule 26)."
